title: 820-3536 not booting
message:
Got a macbook in today, its liquid damaged, the battery is swollen and doesn’t work.


The board has no corrosion whatsoever  and looks new, doesn’t look like its been cleaned. no burned components etc. 

put a new battery in and its charging fine. the mac just wouldn’t boot. fan spins, cpu cold to the touch,  tried smc. PRAM doesn’t work, no chime.

any suggestions?

title: 820-3536 not booting
message: CPU Vcore? Check corrosion in U6100, U1900 area. Also check if USB mouse lights up, could be dead LCD too.

title: 820-3536 not booting
message: What happened? If you slipped with a probe or something I cannot diagnose that from here. Are you using a 60W charger? Is there corrosion under the SMC? Picture of U6100 area? J6100 checked for corrosion?
